<h1>Chapter 2
<br>Document Model Issues for Hypermedia</h1>
<p>
<hr width="80%">
</center>

 <H1>Abstract</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>There are many different systems for creating hypermedia
documents-&#062 this leads to problems such as:
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>comparing documents created by different systems , describing the
information captured by a document for
<LI>long-term storage and future playback
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>solution for these problems is a hypermedia document model, its
components are
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>hierarchical and linking structure
<LI>spatial and temporal relations
<LI>transportability and retrieval
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Amsterdam Hypermedia Model created by authors
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>it is a basis for a comprehensive authoring environment</UL></UL></P>
<P></P> 
</P>



